President Cyril Ramaphosa will engage will the South African National Editors’ Forum on Sunday. The President will engage with the media as South Africa battles the COVID-19 pandemic. JOHANNESBURG - President Cyril Ramaphosa says he was saddened by the death of eNCA cameraman Lungile Tom. Tom died earlier this month after a battle with COVID-19. "I was very saddened when I heard that your colleague Lungile Tom had passed away," Ramaphosa said. Ramaphosa made the remarks during a virtual engagement with members of the South African National Editors' Forum. WATCH: Tribute to eNCA cameraman Lungile Tom The president says journalists have played a huge role in the fight against COVID-19. Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.